    ],
    "system_prompt": "You must explicitly call add_conversation_metadata tool whenever the metadata values (defined by the different input(s) to this tool and their descriptions) have changed. Ensure to keep the metadata up to date with information during your task particularly at the end when you've completed the task, before reporting back on your outcome, or calling another agent. Remember, if new information hasn't changed the metadata values there is no need to update them.",
    "read_metadata_system_prompt": "Use the read_conversation_metadata tool ONLY when you need to access current metadata values that are not already available in your conversation context. Do not call this tool if metadata information is already present in the conversation history or context. Only use it when you specifically need to refresh or retrieve metadata that is missing from your current context to make informed decisions or take actions."
  },
  "memory": {
    "enabled": true,
    "memory_level": "user",
    "add_memory_prompt": "You have the add_agent_memory tool to save important information to your long-term memory. Use this tool to save user preferences, personal facts, or custom instructions. To create a new memory, provide memory_text, category, importance, and reasoning. To update an existing memory, provide memory_id along with new memory_text, category, importance, and reasoning. Always explain your reasoning for adding or updating this memory. Save information ONLY if ALL criteria are met: it's likely to be referenced in future conversations, it's user-specific context (not general knowledge), it cannot be easily re-derived, and it represents a meaningful change from existing memories. Don't save temporary data, one-time requests, general knowledge, or debugging details. Keep memories concise, update existing memories instead of creating duplicates, and use \"high\" importance sparingly.",
    "delete_memory_prompt": "You have the delete_agent_memory tool to remove outdated or incorrect information from your long-term memory. Use this tool to remove memories when explicitly asked by the user, delete outdated or incorrect memories (requires memory_id), or clean up duplicate or conflicting memories. Only delete memories when necessary and consider updating instead of deleting when possible.",
